  • 4th Degree Sexual Assault [Modifiers: Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "A"], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.225(3m).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

BRANCH 38 FOR BRANCH 12:
Defendant Tyrone Wilder in court with attorney Eugene E Detert.  Defendant Tyrone Wilder in custody.  Jennifer Williams for Erin M Karshen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
On motion of the State, Court ordered charge amended to 4th Degree Sexual Assault, contrary to Wisconsin Statutes section(s) 940.225(3m), 939.51(3)(a), a Class A Misdemeanor.
Filed, original amended information; copy served on defendant.  Defendant acknowledges receipt of information, waives formal reading, pleads no contest.

BRANCH 38 FOR BRANCH 12:
As to the Amended Information: Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  The Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon not to possess any firearms/body armor.    Court further advised defendant of voting ineligibility.     Court ordered defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.    On motion of both parties, Court ordered a presentence investigation without a recommendation.  Order for Presentence Investigation received and filed; copy to Probation Dept.  Jury trial scheduled for 07/07/2014 vacated.  Court ordered case adjourned for sentencing to Br. 12.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for August 21, 2014 at 03:00 pm.

Parties contacted the court.  Parties have reached a resolution in this matter and request a plea hearing prior to the trial date.  Br 12 is down the week of 7/1/2014.  Br 38 will hear the plea for Br 12.   Case is adjourned to Br 38 for plea hearing on 7/2/2014 at 8:30 a.m.   Deputy Court Clerk kmh.
